=== Pronunciation ===
[[Category:Hebrew language]]
בּשׂר / bâśâr / baw-sawr'
=== Etymology ===

From {{HH|1319}}; 
=== Noun ===
[[flesh]] (from its freshness); by extension body, person; also (by euphemism) the pudenda of a man: - body, [fat, lean] flesh [-ed], kin, [man-] kind, + nakedness, self, skin.